By Kofoworola Belo-Osagie  Junior Secondary School (JSS) pupils now have their own radio instruction programmes that would air on Naija FM 107.2. The Programme is a collaboration between the Lagos State Ministry of Education and the South Saharan Social Development Organisation. In a statement, the Education Commissioner Mrs. Folasade Adefisayo said the programmes to be aired from Monday for one hour daily (12noon -1pm) would feature four subjects, namely: English Studies, Mathematics, Basic Science and Civic Education. She added that the teachings are to commence from Monday, 6th of April, 2020, running from 12 noon to 1pm daily. She urged parents to inform their wards and make the best use of the quality teachings and educative programme. The radio programme follows the one for senior secondary school pupils airing on WAZOBIA radio and television stations.